    <text id="R155940T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Confederate Adjutant General Samuel Cooper writes General Joseph E. Johnston that
                    he can expect troops to arrive from Staunton in November, 1861.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Gen. JOSEPH E. JOHNSTON,<lb/> Cmdg. Department of
                        Northern Virginia, Centreville, Va.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-11-07">November 7, 1861.</date>
                        <name type="place">RICHMOND,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>SIR:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your letter of the 4th instant has been submitted to the Secretary of War, and I
                    am instructed to inform you that the number of troops to be sent to Staunton,
                    Va., under instructions to Brig.-Gen. Loring, of the 5th inst. (copy herewith),
                    is estimated at between 6,000 and 7,000 effective men. It is designed by the
                    Secretary of war that this force be sent to your command on its arrival at
                    Staunton, and orders to that effect will be given, unless some unforeseen event
                    should required its presence in a different quarter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully, &amp;c.,</salute>
                    <signed>S. COOPER,<lb/> Adjutant and Inspector Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
